<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,726,1147]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,726,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[314,414,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 132 – 134" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[224,1361,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[224,1362,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 132 – 134. Hephathus spp., distribution maps: 132 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer); 133 ― H. freyi (Fieber); 134 ― H. achilleae Mityaev." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244513/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Fig. 
<number box="[368,414,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="134.0">134</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eastern Europe northwards to Fennoscandia and Baltic Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Soderman" box="[1168,1424,726,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Soderman, G., Gillerfors, G. &amp; Endrestol, A. (2009) An annotated catalogue of the Auchenorrhyncha of Northern Europe (Insecta, Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha et Cicadomorpha). Cicadina, 10, 33 - 69. Available from: http: // public. bibliothek. unihalle. de / index. php / cicadina / article / view / 525 / 530 (accessed 14 July 2015)" type="journal article" year="2009">
Söderman et al., 
<number box="[1364,1424,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[151,244,762,787]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, European 
<collectingCountry box="[369,446,762,787]" name="Russia" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Russia</collectingCountry>
, North Caucasus, Transcaucasia, steppe zone of Northern and Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1237,1371,762,787]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,726,1147]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,798,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Species identification.</emphasis>
Four 
<typeStatus box="[531,638,799,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">paratypes</typeStatus>
with the labels “Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[928,1062,798,823]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, env. Katon-Karagai, the foothill plain, milfoil [
<taxonomicName box="[321,414,834,859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Achillea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,414,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Achillea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.], 
<date box="[484,623,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1961-07-28">
<number box="[484,514,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="28.0">28</number>
.VII. 
<number box="[565,623,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</date>
, I.D. Mityaev” deposited in Zoological Museum of M.V. Lomonosov Moscow State University were investigated (
<figureCitation box="[654,819,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 98 – 131" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[207,1369,202,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1376,193,1873]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 98 – 131. Hephathus spp., face. 98 – 106 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer) (100 ― specimen from Bavaria); 107 – 121 ― H. freyi (Fieber) (115 – 121 ― large specimens from Iran and Central Tien-Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 122 – 131 ― H. achilleae Mityaev (124, 128 ― paratypes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244512/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[717,819,871,895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="124.128">124, 128</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="541" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,726,1147]" box="[199,1436,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Remark.</emphasis>
Apparently, some previous records of 
<taxonomicName box="[737,838,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[737,838,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Eastern Europe and 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1206,906,931]" name="Russia" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Russia</collectingCountry>
refer to this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,726,1147]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
One male (
<typeStatus box="[333,435,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">holotype</typeStatus>
, Figs. 
<number box="[519,590,943,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="78.0" valueMax="79.0" valueMin="77.0">77–79</number>
) and one female (
<figureCitation box="[814,954,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1763,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,224,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80 ― Hephathus nanus (Herrich-Schäffer), lateral view, specimen from Bavaria; 81 – 82 ― H. achilleae Mityaev, same (81 ― specimen from North Caucasus, 82 ― specimen from Moscow Area); 83 – 94 ― H. freyi (Fieber), same (83 – 84 ― specimens from Iran, 85 ― specimen from Morocco, 86 ― specimen from West Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan, 87 – 88 ― specimens from Southern European Russia, 89 – 94 ― specimens from Kekemeren River Valley, Central Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 95 – 97 ― H. orientalis Linnavuori (95 ― lateral view, 96 ― face, 97 ― labels)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[882,954,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="96.0" valueMax="97.0" valueMin="95.0">95–97</number>
</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1953" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1953" box="[1010,1369,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1010,1157,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[1169,1369,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1953) Contributions to the Hemipterous fauna of Palestine II. Annales Entomologici Fennici, 19, 119 - 124." type="journal article" year="1953">
Linnavuori, 
<number box="[1313,1369,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were investigated. This form was originally described as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1953" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1953" box="[870,1193,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[870,972,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. nanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[987,1185,978,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1953) Contributions to the Hemipterous fauna of Palestine II. Annales Entomologici Fennici, 19, 119 - 124." type="journal article" year="1953">
Linnavuori, 
<number box="[1128,1185,978,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and later regarded as separate species (
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[348,549,1014,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1962) Hemiptera of Israel III. Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae &quot; Vanamo &quot;, 24 (3), 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1962">
Linnavuori, 
<number box="[489,549,1014,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Externally and in the shape of male genitalia, it is indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[410,609,1050,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1962) Hemiptera of Israel III. Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae &quot; Vanamo &quot;, 24 (3), 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1962">
Linnavuori, 
<number box="[550,609,1050,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, it is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[806,907,1050,1075]" name="Palestine" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Palestine</collectingCountry>
and monophagous on 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1371,1050,1075]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sanguineus">
<emphasis box="[1166,1371,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Rubus sanguineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This may indicate that 
<taxonomicName box="[356,499,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[356,499,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a separate biological species. This species is tentatively retained as a valid, but investigation of male calling signals will be necessary to elucidate its status.
</paragraph>
